  "text": "Proliferation of the modulated cells was assessed by BrdU assay, in which MCF10A cells were incubated with BrdU for 4 hours and analyzed by flow cytometry 48 hours after infection. Notch activation increased the actively proliferating cell population, as expected [CITATION_1] , with an increase in BrdU positive population from 4% in \"Control-Control\" group to 10% in \"NICD -Control\" group (Fig 2C) . When Notch cannot upregulate IRF6, the percentage of actively proliferating cells dropped to 3%, compared to \"NICD-Control\" group. Silencing of IRF6 only, did not affect BrdU incorporation rate (Fig 2C) . Cell viability was assessed by MTT assay, in which the absorbance of formazan precipitate is correlated with the number of the alive cells [CITATION_2] . In response to IRF6 abrogation cell viability was reduced by 15% in Notch activated cells (Fig 2D) . Thus, IRF6 upregulation is required for Notch induced cell proliferation.",
